-- Sanlam Is Concerned About Investec Executive Pay, Bus. Day Says
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2012-05-25T05:16:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-25/sanlam-is-concerned-about-investec-executive-pay-bus-day-says.html
Sanlam Investment Management, which
owns 5.2 percent of Investec Ltd., is concerned about executive
pay levels at the bank, Business Day reported, citing  Richard
Anderson , head of corporate governance at Sanlam.  Anderson was reacting to a Citibank report that said
Investec had overpaid for acquisitions and is raising pay even
as earnings fall, the Johannesburg-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
